<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-ZCk4z3tpY9UfDmplKrCeUg" name="uam_key_principles,__TrU8NBOEdymj4NXv8-FYA" guid="-ZCk4z3tpY9UfDmplKrCeUg" authors="DW Enstrom" changeDate="2015-10-14T14:01:58.531-0400" changeDescription="Revised for UAM" version="2.0.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Key_Principles&quot; name=&quot;XE_Key_Principles&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IT architecture activities typically involve a small team working with a variety of business domain and business&#xD;
    process experts that understand the &quot;system&quot; (i.e. the enterprise or a portion thereof) in question.&amp;nbsp;Like software&#xD;
    development this&amp;nbsp;it's not an engineering discipline&amp;nbsp;from the standpoint of well-defined&amp;nbsp;principles and&#xD;
    methods based on hard facts and centuries of application. It still is therefore a &quot;craft&quot; requiring years of study and&#xD;
    practice before one gets good at it. The principles and practices defined here are an attempt to shorten this learning&#xD;
    curve by&amp;nbsp;describing the keys to success.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;UAM has also define an approach that tries to make IT&#xD;
    architecture more of an engineering discipline, however it is just a start in hopefully the right direction.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_UAM__key_principles&quot; name=&quot;XE_UAM__key_principles&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    With the advent of corporate computer networks, and the explosive growth and use of the Internet, enterprises and the&#xD;
    many computer systems and their contained applications are no longer stand-alone contained black boxes. Everything, yes&#xD;
    absolutely everything, is connected to everything else these days. This has enabled more dynamic and agile enterprises,&#xD;
    but has resulted in the need for and greatly complicated the job of the enterprise or domain architect. No longer can&#xD;
    projects go off and do their own thing, they have&amp;nbsp;to be architected and designed to fit into the larger enterprise&#xD;
    (or even Internet) context. This also means that the enterprise needs to have an IT&amp;nbsp;blueprint—integrated IT&#xD;
    architectures. &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Today, Information Technology (IT)&amp;nbsp;is more and more a&amp;nbsp;key business enabler—so our approach&amp;nbsp;to IT must be&#xD;
    more and more business-oriented and&amp;nbsp;business-driven.&amp;nbsp;The following principles&amp;nbsp;articulate &lt;em>best&#xD;
    practices&lt;/em> for this broad enterprise (and Internet) context and highly integrated and evolving business-driven IT.&#xD;
    They are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN-LEFT: 2em&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;ul>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_core_business_E1F9779E.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_MHnAMECfEeOfR_FtRm9PUg&quot;>Focus on the Core Business&lt;/a>&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_get_level_right_279D36FB.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_7d1BgNEOEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ&quot;>Get the Levels Right&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_quality_thru_tools_38260A4A.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_MS3hINJxEdyTfZVjf0InKw&quot;>Quality Through Tools&lt;/a>&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_deconflict_needs_A76CF077.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_yJz1QNEKEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ&quot;>Deconflict Business Needs&lt;/a>&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_do_the_math_C1C555B6.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_8ld5QECkEeOfR_FtRm9PUg&quot;>Do the Math&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_glossary_7C5D47E2.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_P6kB4NEDEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ&quot;>Define a Robust Glossary&lt;/a>&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_evolve_to_complex_A93F5EB5.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;_AMVHENEGEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ&quot;>Evolve to a Complex Model&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Each&amp;nbsp;of these pages presents&amp;nbsp;one of the above&amp;nbsp;principles, emphasizing:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN-LEFT: 2em&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;ul>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            The &lt;em>benefits&lt;/em> derived from applying the principle,&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            The &lt;em>pattern&lt;/em> of behavior and usage&amp;nbsp;that best embodies the principle, and&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            The most recognizable &lt;strong>&quot;&lt;/strong>&lt;em>anti-patterns&lt;/em>&lt;strong>&quot;&lt;/strong> or behaviors contrary to the&#xD;
            principle, which can harm the effort.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;/div></mainDescription>
